Another tricky question, very common with PANW tests.

While I agree with "A", if you go to "Monitor > Decryption" you will see an "Error" and "Error Index" column (if you don't see it, you can enable it).

The Traffic log will only tell you if a session was decrypted or not, but no-decrypted traffic doesn't always mean a failure, it could often mean there's a decryption policy with action "no decrypt" or an SSL decryption exclusion or an error.

Something to think about...

Explanation:

Dynamic Tag Registration on Palo Alto Networks Next-Generation Firewalls (NGFWs) allows the firewall to automatically assign tags to IP addresses based on information received from external sources. These tags can then be used in security policies for granular control.
The methods to dynamically register tags are:
RESTful API: The firewall can receive tag information from external systems (e.g., cloud platforms, SIEMs, or custom scripts) via RESTful API calls.
VMware API: If the firewall is integrated with VMware environments, it can use the VMware API to dynamically tag virtual machines (VMs) based on attributes like VM names, tags, or other metadata.
User-ID Agent: The User-ID agent can also be used to register tags dynamically by correlating IP addresses with user or group information from directory services (e.g., Active Directory).
